HOUSE BILL 691
P3, C9 6lr1788
By: Delegates Lopez, Kaufman, Spiegel, and Wims
Introduced and read first time: February 2, 2026
Assigned to: Economic Matters
Committee Report: Favorable
House action: Adopted
Read second time: February 28, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 State Government – Procedures – Permitting Efficiency for Housing
3 Development Projects
4 FOR the purpose of requiring certain units in the Executive Branch of State government
5 to adopt procedures to streamline certain permitting processes for housing
6 development projects; requiring the State Housing Ombudsman to ensure
7 consistency between certain permitting processes developed by different units;
8 authorizing the delegation of certain tasks related to the review or approval of
9 permits related to housing construction to certain local governmental units; and
10 generally relating to permitting efficiency for housing development projects.
11 BY renumbering
12 Article – State Government
13 Section 10–1701 and 10–1702 and the subtitle “Subtitle 17. Miscellaneous”
14 to be Section 10–1801 and 10–1802, respectively, and the subtitle “Subtitle 18.
15 Miscellaneous”
16 Annotated Code of Maryland
17 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
18 BY adding to
19 Article – State Government
20 Section 10–1701 through 10–1703 to be under the new subtitle “Subtitle 17.
21 Permitting Efficiency for Housing Development Projects”
22 Annotated Code of Maryland
23 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb0691*

2 HOUSE BILL 691
1 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
2 That Section(s) 10–1701 and 10–1702 and the subtitle “Subtitle 17. Miscellaneous” of
3 Article – State Government of the Annotated Code of Maryland be renumbered to be
4 Section(s) 10–1801 and 10–1802, respectively, and the subtitle “Subtitle 18. Miscellaneous”.
5 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
6 as follows:
7 Article – State Government
8 SUBTITLE 17. PERMITTING EFFICIENCY FOR HOUSING DEVELOPMENT PROJECTS.
9 10–1701.
10 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
11 INDICATED.
12 (B) “HOUSING DEVELOPMENT PROJECT” MEANS THE NEW CONSTRUCTION
13 OR SUBSTANTIAL RENOVATION OF A RESIDENTIAL REAL ESTATE PROJECT.
14 (C) (1) “PERMIT RELATED TO HOUSING CONSTRUCTION” MEANS A
15 PERMIT OR AN APPROVAL REQUIRED BY LAW OR REGULATION TO BE ISSUED BY A
16 UNIT IN THE EXECUTIVE BRANCH OF STATE GOVERNMENT TO A DEVELOPER,
17 CONTRACTOR, OR SUBCONTRACTOR IN ORDER TO COMMENCE, CONTINUE, OR
18 SUPPORT A HOUSING DEVELOPMENT PROJECT.
19 (2) “PERMIT RELATED TO HOUSING CONSTRUCTION” INCLUDES A
20 PERMIT OR AN APPROVAL RELATED TO THE CONSTRUCTION OR EXPANSION OF
21 SUPPORTIVE INFRASTRUCTURE SERVING A HOUSING DEVELOPMENT PROJECT.
22 (D) “STATE HOUSING OMBUDSMAN” MEANS THE INDIVIDUAL DESIGNATED
23 BY THE DEPARTMENT OF HOUSING AND COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT TO
24 FACILITATE NAVIGATION THROUGH LOCAL, STATE, AND FEDERAL PERMITTING
25 PROCESSES.
26 10–1702.
27 (A) EACH UNIT IN THE EXECUTIVE BRANCH OF STATE GOVERNMENT THAT
28 IS RESPONSIBLE FOR ISSUING A PERMIT RELATED TO HOUSING CONSTRUCTION
29 SHALL ADOPT PROCEDURES TO STREAMLINE THE PERMITTING PROCESS IN
30 ACCORDANCE WITH THIS SECTION.

HOUSE BILL 691 3
1 (B) A STREAMLINED PERMITTING PROCESS ADOPTED UNDER THIS SECTION
2 SHALL, AT A MINIMUM:
3 (1) TO THE EXTENT FEASIBLE, ALLOW FOR THE CONCURRENT FILING
4 AND ADJUDICATION OF MULTIPLE PERMITS OR APPROVALS RELATED TO A
5 PARTICULAR HOUSING DEVELOPMENT PROJECT;
6 (2) IN CASES IN WHICH CONCURRENT FILING AND ADJUDICATION IS
7 NOT FEASIBLE, PROVIDE FOR THE PREDICTABLE SEQUENCING OF FILINGS AND
8 ADJUDICATIONS; AND
9 (3) ESTABLISH A FRAMEWORK THAT ALLOWS FOR THE EXPEDITED
10 REVIEW OF PERMITS RELATED TO HOUSING CONSTRUCTION, INCLUDING CLEAR
11 ESCALATION AND PRIORITIZATION PATHWAYS.
12 (C) IN DEVELOPING A STREAMLINED PERMITTING PROCESS UNDER THIS
13 SECTION, A UNIT SHALL CONSULT WITH:
14 (1) THE UNIT’S PERMITTING OPERATIONS STAFF;
15 (2) RELEVANT STAKEHOLDERS, INCLUDING ENTITIES THAT
16 FREQUENTLY APPLY FOR PERMITS; AND
17 (3) THE STATE HOUSING OMBUDSMAN.
18 (D) TO THE EXTENT FEASIBLE, THE STATE HOUSING OMBUDSMAN SHALL
19 ENSURE CONSISTENCY BETWEEN THE STREAMLINED PERMITTING PROCESSES
20 DEVELOPED BY DIFFERENT UNITS UNDER THIS SECTION.
21 10–1703.
22 NOTWITHSTANDING ANY OTHER PROVISION OF LAW, A UNIT IN THE
23 EXECUTIVE BRANCH OF STATE GOVERNMENT MAY, BY AGREEMENT WITH A COUNTY
24 OR MUNICIPALITY, DELEGATE TO AN APPROPRIATE LOCAL GOVERNMENTAL UNIT
25 ANY TASK RELATED TO THE REVIEW OR APPROVAL OF PERMITS RELATED TO
26 HOUSING CONSTRUCTION WITHIN THE COUNTY OR MUNICIPALITY.
27 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That on or before December 1,
28 2027, the State Housing Ombudsman within the Department of Housing and Community
29 Development shall report to the Senate Committee on Education, Energy, and the
30 Environment and the House Government, Labor, and Elections Committee, in accordance
31 with § 2–1257 of the State Government Article, on the development and implementation of
32 the streamlined permitting processes required by this Act.

4 HOUSE BILL 691
1 SECTION 4. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
2 October 1, 2026.
Approved:
